<paragraph id="FD1036FD9064FF99B4AC12F7FB5CF9EE" blockId="0.[151,1436,1479,1540]" pageId="0" pageNumber="493">
<emphasis id="CFDBEAEF9064FF99B4AC12F7FEECFA35" box="[151,268,1479,1503]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="493" reason="1">
<emphasis id="CFDBEAEF9064FF99B4AC12F7FEE5FA35" bold="true" box="[151,261,1479,1503]" pageId="0" pageNumber="493">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Male tenth abdominal tergite significantly prolonged and enlarged backwards, apical area bifurcate; cercus short and stout; genitalia sclerotized and elongated, surpassing posterior margin of subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
